  "abstract": "  Let a flow $T_t$ preserve an ergodic probability measure $\\mu$, $\\int\nf\\,d\\mu=0$, and $\\mu(A)>0$. Then for almost all $x\\in A$, for which $f(x)\\neq\n0$, there is a sequence ${t_k}\\to \\infty$ such that $T_{t_k}x\\in A$ and\n$\\int_0^{t_k} f(T_sx)ds=0$.\n",
